"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747743","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Ministry of Defence is critically reviewing all activities and functions undertaken by the civilian workforce. We will review and test, based on value for money assessments, how these activities and functions could best be done in the future. The achievement of the Department's objectives, including the delivery of front-line operational capabilities, remains our priority. Alternative delivery models will be evaluated.</p><p>The Department outsourced 4,090 staff between Financial Year (FY) 2012-13 and FY2016-17 (inclusive), broken down by year as follows: FY2012-13 (380 staff); FY2013-14 (zero staff); FY2014-15 (2,355 staff); FY2015-16 (1,130 staff) and FY2016-17 (225 staff).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","2552 ; 2556","2017-07-11T16:15:38.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747743/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747743/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747743/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Ministry of Defence: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of planned civilian redundancies within his Department on the operational capabilities of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2549"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747744","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p>The MOD has strict rules on hospitality, including the purchase of alcohol. Public funds are not to be used for 'drinks only' functions, other than at official receptions.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-10T15:50:04.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747744/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747744/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747744/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Ministry of Defence: Wines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on wine in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747745","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>Work is on-going in the Ministry of Defence, led by Joint Forces Command, to determine the detailed requirements underpinning any future overland capability programme.</p><p>A number of space-based, manned and unmanned aircraft solutions, including the development of a sensor for integration onto P-8A, are being explored as part of this work.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","2555","2017-07-11T15:11:18.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747745/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747745/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Military Aircraft: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department plans to procure a new platform to enable the RAF to maintain its wide-area surveillance capability after the Sentinel R1 fleet is retired in 2021.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747746","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The information is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-07-10T15:49:41.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747746/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747746/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747746/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Ministry of Defence: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on hospitality for foreign (a) military personnel and (b) civilian defence officials in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747747","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>The historic source of the Gurkhas goes back to 1815. The Brigade has conducted itself with distinction worldwide as part of Army operations.</p><p>The full cost of recruiting Nepali citizens into the Brigade of Gurkhas in each of the last five financial years (FY) is shown below:</p><p>FY 2012-13 - £838,500.00</p><p>FY 2013-14 - £898,400.00</p><p>FY 2014-15 - £900,100.00</p><p>FY 2015-16 - £972,000.00</p><p>FY 2016-17 - £970,100.00</p><p>These totals cover the complete costs to the British Army for running recruitment each year in Nepal, including military and civilian personnel, accommodation, medical, clothing, rations and transportation. These costs reflect the unique recruiting process conducted in Nepal.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-11T16:04:43.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747747/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747747/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Gurkhas: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost was of recruiting foreign personnel into the Brigade of Gurkhas in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747748","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>A review determined that increased involvement of industry in Defence's fire and rescue capability would improve value for money whilst maintaining the protection of vital assets. The Ministry of Defence is currently running a single commercial competition for fire and rescue services considered suitable for delivery by industry, including HM Naval Base Clyde and a number of British Armed Forces airfields. The aim is to award a contract by early 2018.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-07-11T15:47:35.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747748/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747748/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747748/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Ministry of Defence: Fire and Rescue Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans are in place to outsource his Department's fire and rescue services on airfields and dockyards.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","2548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747749","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-06","<p>There are currently no plans to require Highways England to publish the minutes of its Board meetings.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-06T14:03:49.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747749/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747749/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747749/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-03","Highways England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to require Highways England to publish the minutes of its board meetings.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","2400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747750","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-06","<p>The one percent pay cap applies to the accident investigation branches. It does not apply to the CAA, which is a public corporation and is not covered by public sector pay arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>Highways England and HS2 Ltd have agreed separate pay flexibilities outside of the one percent cap with HM Treasury.</p><p> </p><p>From its creation in 2002 as a company classified to the private sector Network Rail did not have a public sector pay cap and since its reclassification to the public sector Network Rail has agreed separate pay flexibilities outside of the one percent cap with HM Treasury.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-07-06T14:16:14.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747750/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747750/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-03","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the one per cent public sector pay cap applies to employees of (a) Highways England, (b) Network Rail, (c) the Civil Aviation Authority, (d) the investigation branches for air, marine and rail accidents and (e) HS2 Ltd.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","2398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747751","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-06","<p>As a government organisation, Network Rail’s expenditure is recorded following rules in the European System of Accounts 2010 (ESA10). My Department has agreed with HM Treasury that those asset sales classified as deficit-reducing under ESA10 definitions can fund expenditure on rail enhancements (expenditure which in turn classifies as deficit-increasing under ESA10 definitions).</p><p> </p><p>The Department holds regular discussions with HM Treasury on a wide range of topics, including Network Rail’s asset sales programme.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-06T13:59:33.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747751/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747751/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-03","Network Rail: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to page 5 of the minutes of Network Rail's Board meeting of 28 September 2016, what the accounting reason referred to is which requires HM Treasury in turn to require the proceeds from asset sales to count towards general deficit reduction; and what recent discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on the proceeds of Network Rail's asset sales programme.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","2399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747752","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-06","<p>The Department is in the process of producing new Road Traffic Forecasts to inform the development of the 2<sup>nd</sup> Roads Investment Strategy. These forecasts will reflect the impact of all major transport investment decisions made by the government since the last forecasts were produced in 2015, including the cycling and walking investment strategy. The new Road Traffic Forecasts will be published in due course.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-06T13:54:54.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747752/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747752/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747752/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-03","Cycling and Walking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, with reference to the Answer of 30 June 2016 to Question 41299, on cycling and walking, and the Answer of 13 June 2016 to Question 39847, on travel, what the potential effects are of the cycling and walking investment strategy on the figures given in the Answer to Question 39847.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","2396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747753","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-06","<p>It is not the Department’s policy to migrate the current Network Rail website to the GOV.UK website.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-07-06T14:11:57.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747753/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747753/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747753/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-03","Network Rail: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether it is his policy to migrate the current Network Rail website to the gov.uk website.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","2397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747754","Department for Education","false","2017-07-14","<p>Expanding universal infant free school meals (UIFSM) to all primary school children is not something the government plans to do and we have not examined this fully. However, initial costings suggest there would be an additional cost of between £700m to £900m per year, increasing the overall cost of UIFSM to between £1.3 billion and £1.5 billion per year.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-07-14T13:38:52.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747754/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747754/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747754/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-03","Primary Education: Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the cost of introducing free school meals to all primary school children.","false","Biography information for Alex Burghart","Brentwood and Ongar","Alex Burghart","2452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747755","Department for Education","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Department for Education has not assessed the cost of restoring the Education Maintenance Allowance for 16 to 18 year olds in each parental income decile.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-11T15:42:52.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747755/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747755/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-03","Education Maintenance Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the cost of restoring the education maintenance allowance for 16 to 18-year-olds in each parental income decile.","false","Biography information for Alex Burghart","Brentwood and Ongar","Alex Burghart","2453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747756","Department for International Development","false","2017-07-11","<p>The UK is committed to focusing on reaching the most marginalised children; including those with disabilities. We have publicly committed; to ensure all educational construction directly funded by DFID is fully accessible; and to work with partners to improve data on children with disabilities and special educational needs, both in- and out-of-education.</p><p>For example in the Middle East and North Africa we are working closely with partners to identify children with disabilities and to understand their needs. In Jordan we have trained more than 11,000 teachers, supervisors and administrators on how to deliver effective reading and maths instruction including skills to identify and assess children with a disability in their classroom. In Lebanon, through the Ministry of Education, we are supporting teacher training, differentiated learning and other measures to create more inclusive school environments, as well as tracking results around referral of children and youth with special needs.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-07-11T16:39:49.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747756/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747756/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-07-03","Humanitarian Aid: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans her Department has in place to include disability in humanitarian education relief.","false","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","2545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747757","Home Office","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Human Rights Act 1998 requires that primary and subordinate legislation must be given effect in a way that is compatible with the Convention rights defined in Act.</p><p> </p><p>Detainees in the immigration detention estate, including those in Dungavel immigration removal centre (IRC), must be treated in accordance with the Detention Centre Rules 2001, the operating standards for IRCs and Detention Services Orders.</p><p> </p><p>Service providers for IRCs are contractually required to comply with all relevant UK legislation.</p><p> </p><p>IRCs are subject to statutory oversight by Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector of Prisons and by Independent Monitoring Boards who are both members of the National Preventative Mechanism comprising a group of independent bodies which monitor the treatment of and conditions for detainees.</p><p> </p><p>This contributes to the UK’s response to its international obligations under the Optional Protocol to the UN Convention against Torture and other Cruel, Inhuman or Degrading Treatment or Punishment (OPCAT).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-10T13:02:32.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747757/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747757/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-03","Dungavel House Immigration Removal Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what procedures are in place to ensure human rights legislation is complied with in respect of detainees in Dungavel Immigration Removal Centre.","true","Biography information for Dr Lisa Cameron","East Kilbride, Strathaven and Lesmahagow","Dr Lisa Cameron","2563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747758","Scotland Office","false","2017-07-10","<p>Building on the city and growth deals we have signed across Scotland, we will bring forward a Borderlands Growth Deal to secure economic improvements for the people who live and work in our Borderlands region. The Scotland Office will work with the Department for Communities and Local Government, the Scottish Government, and Local Authorities on both sides of the border to identify proposals that will best support the economy of the region, and we look forward to hearing local partners’ ambitions for the area as work progresses.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-07-10T14:33:17.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747758/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747758/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-07-03","Local Growth Deals: Borderlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what progress the Government has made on the delivery of the borderlands Growth Deal.","false","Biography information for John Lamont","Berwickshire, Roxburgh and Selkirk","John Lamont","2511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747759","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-06","<p>We have carried out an overarching review of the probation system to improve outcomes for offenders and communities while making sure public protection remains our top priority. This has influenced the changes to how CRCs are paid and held to account. More detailed work is ongoing and we will provide an update on the review in due course.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-07-06T15:52:05.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747759/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747759/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-07-03","Offenders: Rehabilitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he plans to publish the findings of his Department's review into Transforming Rehabilitation.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","2538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747760","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-06","<p>Starring up is the term used to define the early transition process whereby young people under the age of 18 can be moved into the young adult estate prior to their eighteenth birthday. The starring up process can be used for a range of reasons, but past usage has mainly been in relating to the management of disruptive or violent behaviour or transfers to Mother and Baby Units.</p><p> </p><p>In practice, the starring up process is rarely used and then only in exceptional circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>Data in relation to the number of young people who were starred-up into the young adult estate in each of the last three years (by the establishment they were starred-up from) is provided in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMPPS under 18 YOI</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cookham</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feltham</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Werrington</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wetherby</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>To date, the data for the current year (2017) is:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMPPS under 18 YOI</p></td><td><p>2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cookham</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feltham</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Werrington</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wetherby</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-07-06T10:37:29.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747760/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747760/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-07-03","Young Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many under-18 year olds have been starred up in each prison in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","2539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747761","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-07-06","<p>We have undertaken an overarching review of probation, looking at the standards we set for providers and how we hold them to account. We have already made some changes to how CRCs are paid so they can focus on activities that best rehabilitate offenders and keep society safe. The details of these changes are commercially sensitive, however the contract modification notices are published online at the Official Journal for the European Union.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-07-06T14:56:33.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747761/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747761/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-07-03","Community Rehabilitation Companies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what changes his Department has made to the funding of community rehabilitation companies.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","2540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747762","Home Office","false","2017-07-06","<p>I am sorry but the information you have requested is not included in statistics published by the Home Office.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-06T15:29:36.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747762/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747762/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747762/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-03","Visas: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many visa applications made in Scotland were (a) rejected as a result of the income threshold regulations and (b) granted an appeal in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","2422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747763","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-06","<p>All Tornado GR4 aircraft have been fitted with the Traffic Alert and Collision Avoidance System. This work was completed, as planned, by the end of 2016. The system is now in routine use and has been very well received by RAF Tornado GR4 aircrew.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-06T16:18:33.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747763/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747763/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747763/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","Tornado Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what progress his Department has made on implementing recommendation 1.5.7(a) of the Military Aviation Authority inquiry, published on 30 June 2014, to equip the Tornado GR4 with a collision warning system.","false","Biography information for Douglas Ross","Moray","Douglas Ross","2561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747764","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The RAF is committed to equipping all its Typhoon aircraft with a collision warning system. Under current plans as part of a phased programme Tranche 2 and Tranche 3 aircraft will be fitted with a system by mid 2019. Studies into fitting a collision warning system to Tranche 1 aircraft are ongoing.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","2559","2017-07-10T14:15:59.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747764/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747764/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747764/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department plans for all Typhoon aircrafts to be fitted with a collision warning system; and what the timescale for fitting that system is.","false","Biography information for Douglas Ross","Moray","Douglas Ross","2560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747765","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The RAF is committed to equipping all its Typhoon aircraft with a collision warning system. Under current plans as part of a phased programme Tranche 2 and Tranche 3 aircraft will be fitted with a system by mid 2019. Studies into fitting a collision warning system to Tranche 1 aircraft are ongoing.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","2560","2017-07-10T14:16:00.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747765/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747765/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747765/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-03","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what timetable his Department has set for the feasibility study on introducing a collision warning system on Typhoon aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Ross","Moray","Douglas Ross","2559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748313","Women and Equalities","false","2017-07-06","<p>The right to Shared Parental Leave and the right to request flexible working help share caring responsibilities more fairly in families so that women can fulfil their potential at work. We are doubling the childcare entitlement for working parents of 3 and 4 year olds from 15 to 30 hours a week from September 2017. We have also allocated £5 million to help people return to work after a break in employment, the majority of whom will be women.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-06T16:53:32.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748313/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748313/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748313/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-07-03","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps the Government is taking to open up more work opportunities for women.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","900273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748719","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-06","<p>Ministerial colleagues and I regularly engage with business stakeholders and policy makers in Commonwealth partner countries.</p><p>In March, my noble Friend the Minister of State for Trade Policy (Lord Price) and I met over 20 visiting trade ministers at the inaugural Commonwealth Trade Ministers' Meeting. We discussed strengthening collaboration and deepening intra-Commonwealth trade and investment.</p><p>We are now preparing for the Commonwealth Summit in 2018.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-06T10:47:52.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748719/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748719/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748719/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03","Overseas Trade: Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, What recent discussions he has had with his counterparts in other Commonwealth countries on the future of trade and investment between the UK and those countries.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","900259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748890","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-06","<p>As part of our committment to hear from every sector and region in the UK, DExEU Ministers continue to engage closely with organisations across the agriculture and fishing industries, to enable us to understand issues for the sectors and to identify potential post-exit opportunities.</p><p>We have spoken to a range of organisations including the National Federation of Fishermen's Organisations, and the National Farmers’ Union and will continue to listen to workers in the industry, trade organisations, producers and the public as negotiations progress.</p><p>Leaving the EU presents a major opportunity for the UK agriculture and fishing industries. The Government will be able to design new policies which specifically benefit British agriculture, the countryside and the fisheries, and provide better value for money to the British taxpayer.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-06T15:09:00.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748890/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748890/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-07-03","Agriculture and Fisheries: South West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what steps he is taking to (a) engage with and (b) protect the interests of the South West's agricultural and fishing industries during future trade negotiations with the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","900263"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749077","Women and Equalities","false","2017-07-06","<p>My Right Honourable Friend, the Minister for Women and Equalities has advised me that we should celebrate the progress already made: in 2011 there were 152 all-male boards across the FTSE 350; there are now only six.</p><p> </p><p>We need to go further. We are supporting the work of the Hampton-Alexander Review to increase female leadership on boards and crucially in executive positions, and welcome Sir John Parker’s work on increasing ethnic diversity on FTSE boards.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy are also establishing a new Minister-led Diversity and Inclusion Group to help drive progress, and supporting schemes helping talented women get board experience.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-06T16:50:42.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749077/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749077/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749077/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-07-03","Directors: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps the Government is taking to promote diverse representation on boards.","false","Biography information for Gavin Newlands","Paisley and Renfrewshire North","Gavin Newlands","900280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749080","Women and Equalities","false","2017-07-06","<p>Since 2010, the number of women on FTSE boards has more than doubled. The Hampton-Alexander Review has set targets of women holding 33% of FTSE 100 senior leadership positions and 33% of FTSE 350 board positions.</p><p> </p><p>We are also working with the Women’s Business Council to develop tools for the business community, to stimulate culture change. The Women’s Business Council has been enlarged to 20 members, to include more male agents of change and increase national representation.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-06T16:51:21.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749080/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749080/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749080/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-07-03","Managers: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps the Government is taking to promote the role of female leaders in the workplace.","false","Biography information for Mims Davies","Eastleigh","Mims Davies","900282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749099","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-06","<p>The Department for International Trade is engaging widely with industry and civil society, including trade unions, to ensure our future trade policy works for the whole United Kingdom.</p><p>Through regular bilateral meetings, round tables and trade policy seminars we are able to benefit from the knowledge and expertise of a broad range of stakeholders.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-06T16:49:15.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749099/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749099/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749099/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has to consult (a) industry representatives and (b) trades unions before concluding any future trade deals.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","900260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749100","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-06","<p>Implementing the Trade Facilitation Agreement will increase efficiency at the borders of participating members and make it easier and cheaper for UK businesses to export their goods and services across the globe.</p><p>This is a landmark agreement, which demonstrates the UK’s commitment to free trade and to a global rules-based system.</p><p>Once implemented, studies suggest that the agreement will add over £70 billion to the global economy, with a benefit to the UK of up to £1 billion.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-06T16:50:22.983Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749100/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749100/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749100/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the UK of the WTO's Trade Facilitation Agreement.","false","Biography information for David Morris","Morecambe and Lunesdale","David Morris","900268"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749101","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-06","<p>As the UK prepares for a new era outside the EU, we will look to forge even closer trade and commercial ties with the US. American commitment to this goal was reaffirmed during positive meetings I had with the Secretary for Commerce and US Trade Representative in Washington a fortnight ago.</p><p>We agreed to hold a joint working group this month which will begin to lay the groundwork for a possible future UK-US free trade agreement.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-06T16:51:33.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749101/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749101/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749101/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03","Overseas Trade: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what recent steps he has taken to improve trading links with the US.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","900269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749102","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-06","<p>The Department for International Trade is engaging widely with industry and civil society, including trade unions, to ensure our future trade policy works for the whole United Kingdom.</p><p>Through regular bilateral meetings, round tables and trade policy seminars we are able to benefit from the knowledge and expertise of a broad range of stakeholders.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-06T16:48:10.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749102/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749102/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749102/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans he has to consult (a) industry representatives and (b) trades unions before concluding any future trade deals.","false","Biography information for Afzal Khan","Manchester, Gorton","Afzal Khan","900261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749103","Department for International Trade","false","2017-07-06","<p>The Government will create a network of Her Majesty’s Trade Commissioners to head nine new regional overseas posts. These Commissioners will bring together export promotion, investment, and trade policy at our Posts overseas.</p><p> </p><p>It is vital that we consider the various elements of trade together, and the Commissioners will combine this with a deep understanding of their own global region to optimise our trade relationships across the world.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-07-06T16:46:10.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749103/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749103/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/749103/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-03","Trade Promotion: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what his plans are for the appointment of trade commissioners; and what the criteria for their selection and their mandates will be.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","900266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747042","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-04","<p>The pay for an individual public sector worker is affected by several factors including progression pay, allowances and the one per cent pay policy. It will therefore vary by individual. HMT does not collect this data centrally.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-07-04T14:31:01.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747042/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747042/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747042/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-30","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of public sector workers have received a pay rise limited to one per cent since 2010.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","2338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747043","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-07","<p>The Government has made no formal assessment of the impact of the increase of the personal allowance threshold on household incomes. For individuals, a typical basic rate taxpayer will pay £1,005 less income tax in 2017-18 than in 2010-11, and 1.3 million individuals will be taken out of income tax altogether by 2017-18 (compared to 2015-16), as a result of the Government’s action to increase the personal allowance to £11,500 in April 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The pay for an individual public sector worker is affected by several factors including progression pay, allowances and the one per cent pay policy. It will therefore vary by individual. HM Treasury does not collect this data centrally.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-07T10:35:41.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747043/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747043/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747043/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-30","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of the increase in the personal allowance threshold and the one per cent public sector pay cap on household incomes in the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","2339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747044","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Government does not centrally collate data on the proportion of public sector workers paying basic, higher or additional rates of income tax.</p><p> </p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-07-10T11:22:41.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747044/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747044/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747044/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-30","Public Sector: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of public sector workers pay (a) basic rate, (b) higher rate and (c) additional rate income tax.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","2340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747045","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-07","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility (OBR) expect inflation to average 2.4% over 2017 and 2.3% over 2018. Their forecast was reflected in the distributional analysis published alongside Spring Budget 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is taking action to support the lowest income households. This includes increasing the National Living Wage, raising the personal allowance, and freezing fuel duty.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2017-07-07T10:41:04.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747045/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747045/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747045/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-30","Inflation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effect of recent rises in inflation on the standard of living for the lowest income households.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","2341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747046","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-05","<p>In the last year the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office has not received any requests from the Rt Hon. The Lord Patten of Barnes for a meeting.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-05T14:04:19.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747046/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747046/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747046/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-30","Hong Kong: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he has had any meetings with Lord Patton of Barnes in the last year to discuss (a) human rights and the state of democracy in Hong Kong and (b) the Joint British-Sino Declaration.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","2349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747047","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-05","<p>​Senior officials at the Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office plan to meet Anson Chan during her visit.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-05T14:05:55.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747047/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747047/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747047/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-30","Anson Chan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he intends to meet Anson Chan, former Chief Secretary of Hong Kong, while she is visiting the UK.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","2347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747048","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-07-05","<p>The Foreign Secretary issued a Written Ministerial Statement on 29 June to mark the 20th anniversary of the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (<a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statements/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statements/</a>) which outlined our assessment of the 'One Country, Two Systems' principle, as well as referencing specific concerns over its implementation. The UK continues to believe that it is in Hong Kong's best interests that discussion resumes between all parties in Hong Kong in order to make further progress towards a more democratic and accountable system of government, as provided for in the Basic Law.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2017-07-05T14:08:00.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747048/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747048/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747048/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-06-30","Hong Kong: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the state of democracy in Hong Kong.","false","Biography information for Catherine West","Hornsey and Wood Green","Catherine West","2348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747049","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-05","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answers provided to his questions on 4 July 2017 (1932, and 1934).</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-07-05T10:53:03.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747049/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747049/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747049/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-30","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether the Child Maintenance Service is entitled to full access to (a) assessments made and (b) data held by the Child Support Agency.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","2267"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747050","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-07-13","<p>The reciprocal agreement on citizens' rights will apply to the entire United Kingdom, including the devolved administrations. Decisions that are currently made by the devolved administrations will continue to be made by them.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-07-13T14:32:59.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747050/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747050/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747050/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-06-30","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to the policy paper The United Kingdom's Exit from the European Union: Safeguarding the position of EU Citizens living in the UK and UK nationals living in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, whether the reciprocal agreement on citizens' rights change the power of the devolved legislatures.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","2307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747051","Home Office","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Government’s policy paper (Cm 9464), which was laid before Parliament on 26 June, sets out our proposals that European Union (EU) citizens who arrive in the UK before the specified date and have five years’ continuous residence in the UK will be able to apply for UK settled status.</p><p> </p><p>Work is underway to assess the proposed resources and costs required to implement the new settled status scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The details of the settled status scheme will be subject to negotiations and a reciprocal deal with the EU. We will publish further detail on the specifics of the new application process for settled status, including detailed eligibility criteria, in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","2271 ; 2274 ; 2275 ; 2277 ; 2278","2017-07-10T12:54:51.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747051/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747051/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747051/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-30","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the policy paper The United Kingdom's Exit from the European Union: Safeguarding the position of EU Citizens living in the UK and UK nationals living in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, whether non-family members with dependent British adults or children retain the right to reside in the UK following the country's exit from the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","2308"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747053","Home Office","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Government’s policy paper (Cm 9464), which was laid before Parliament on 26 June, sets out our proposals that European Union (EU) citizens who arrive in the UK before the specified date and have five years’ continuous residence in the UK will be able to apply for UK settled status.</p><p> </p><p>Work is underway to assess the proposed resources and costs required to implement the new settled status scheme.</p><p> </p><p>The details of the settled status scheme will be subject to negotiations and a reciprocal deal with the EU. We will publish further detail on the specifics of the new application process for settled status, including detailed eligibility criteria, in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","2271 ; 2275 ; 2277 ; 2278 ; 2308","2017-07-10T12:54:51.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747053/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747053/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/747053/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-30","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Government's publication The United Kingdom's Exit from the European Union: Safeguarding the Position of EU Citizens Living in the UK and UK Nationals Living in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, what estimate she has made of the costs of implementing the proposed immigration system for EU nationals after the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","2274"
